      <head>Valerie [Wally] Violin</head>

      <div>
        <p>Wife of <ref cRef="entity-000913">Moriz Violin</ref>. Valerie and Moriz married on
          November 15, 1912 (OJ 1/11, p. 281); the couple had a daughter, <ref cRef="entity-000911"
            >Genovefa [Eva; Everl]</ref> and a son <ref cRef="entity-000912">Karl [Karli;
            Carli]</ref>.</p>
        <p><figure>
          <head>Valerie Violin, c. 1955 (Diana Windsor)</head>
          <graphic url="ViolinValerie.jpg" xmt:type="thumb-caption" rend="left-img" width="150px"
            height="113px" mimeType="image/jpeg"/>
          <graphic url="ViolinValerie.jpg" xmt:type="full" rend="left-img" width="800px" height="600px"
            mimeType="image/jpeg"/>
          <figDesc>Photograph of Valerie Violin.</figDesc>
        </figure></p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <head>Correspondence</head>
        <p>Correspondence between Schenker and Valerie Violin survives within OJ 6-8, and OJ 15/45.
          No photographs seem to be preserved with those of Moriz in OJ 72/23; however, there are
          photographs in the family possession (see above, and <ref cRef="entity-002938">Violin
            family</ref>)</p>

      </div>
